BIB                  4          9
REACTION   (29-CU-0(N,THS)29-CU-0,COH,AMP)
SAMPLE     In order to estimate the depth of penetration of the
           neutrons in the mirror, copper layers of various
           thickness were deposited in vacuum on 300x80x30 mm
           glass mirrors.
           The thickness of the copper layer varied between
           12x 10**(-6) g/cm2 and 100 x 10**(-6) g/cm2.
MONITOR    None
COMMENT    Measured at lambda =1.161A.
